IBADAN  – The Oyo State Police Command has confirmed the killing of Alhaja Fatimah Awolesu, the only surviving daughter of the late Iyalode of Ibadan land, Alhaja Aminat Abiodun. Alhaja Abiodun was immediate past Iyalode of Ibadanland. Fatimah Awolesu was killed early hours of Wednesday by unknown gunmen in her residence located at Bashorun area of Ibadan. Amotekun Bursts International Human Trafficking, Kidnap… Suspected Cultists Cut Off Man’s Head In Bayelsa Confirming the killing, Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Oyo State Command, Adewale Osifeso, said that the body of the deceased had been deposited at the morgue. He said, “The unfortunate demise of Alhaja Fatima Awolesu ‘f ’ was reported by a family associate to the Police on Wednesday 09/03/2022. “Preliminary investigations revealed that the deceased was attacked at her Bashorun residence by unknown assailants who also inflicted bodily wounds on her. “Crime Scene Investigators have been immediately deployed to Crime Scene for detailed forensic processes and thorough investigations. “Meanwhile, the body of the deceased has been deposited at the State Morgue. POLL “Updates regarding the incident and investigations would be made available in due course, please.”